# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 🤖 TELEGRAM BOT — ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# Bot token from @BotFather
BOT_TOKEN=your_bot_token_here

# Channel username (without @) or ID that users must join
# Example: mychannelname  OR  -1001234567890
FORCE_CHANNEL=your_channel_username

# Comma-separated list of admin Telegram user IDs
# Example: 123456789,987654321
ADMIN_IDS=123456789,987654321

# Bot username (without @) from @BotFather
# Example: MyAwesomeBot
BOT_USERNAME=YourBotUsername

# MongoDB connection string
# Railway provides this automatically if you add MongoDB plugin
# Example: mongodb+srv://user:pass@cluster.mongodb.net/dbname
DATABASE_URL=mongodb://localhost:27017/telegrambot
